A majority of US governors have expressed their support for tax reform and have urged Congress to swiftly pass meaningful tax reform legislation. The governors argue that their states have successfully implemented tax cuts while creating jobs and generating budget surpluses, and they believe that tax reform can work for America as well. They emphasize the need to simplify the tax code, close loopholes, and create a fairer system for businesses and individuals. They also highlight the importance of reducing the burden on middle-class families, encouraging economic growth, and attracting businesses to the United States. The governors believe that tax reform is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity that should not be missed.